message: The previous description is not factually correct and targets other ethnic groups.
The former is factually wrong. Made corrections.

Undid revision 1083546320 by [[Special:Contributions/Joshua Jonathan|Joshua Jonathan]] ([[User talk:Joshua Jonathan|talk]]) LEAD Section is accurate!!!
This edit describes about the religion far better with accurate information and replaces those false claims and descriptions.

I think this is better description of the religion - gives more clear aspects of the religion. Furthermore, uncited claims including Sanamahism to be "animistic", "Shaman-led" religion has been removed. The later two is a false claim. There are of course similarity to a Shaman or Shamanism but this religion is not led by a Shaman. The Maibis are only priestess and not the heads of the religion. Sanamahism is very different from Animistic religions.
changed from British Raj to Princely state (British Raj) which is more appropriate.
Citation to Cheitharol Kumbaba for the list.
Added the time period when Manipur was a Sovereign state(1947-1949 A.D), Bodha Chandra was the only king to rule in this short period of time.
